devdoc.details: SLARegistry is a contract for handling creation of service level agreements and keeping track of the created agreements

AnalyticsReceived(bytes32,bytes32,uint25.details: Event to store a new analytics ipfs hash received

params._ipfsHash: 1. id of the canonical period to be analyzed

SLACreated(address,address).details: event for service level agreement creation logging

params.owner: 2. The address of the owner of the service level agreement
params.sla: 1. The address of the created service level agreement contract

StakingParametersModified(uint256,uint25.details: event to log modifications on the staking parameters

params.burnRate: 3. (burnRate/1000)% of DSLA to be burned after a reward/compensation is paid
params.minimumDSLAStakedTier1: 4. minimum stake of DSLA to enable tier 1 privileges
params.minimumDSLAStakedTier2: 5. minimum stake of DSLA to enable tier 2 privileges
params.minimumDSLAStakedTier3: 6. minimum stake of DSLA to enable tier 3 privileges
params.providerRewardPercentage: 2. percentage of the users pool to be rewarded to the provider

SLACount().details: public view function that returns the total amount of service level agreements

returns._0: uint256, the length of SLA array

addAllowedTokens(address).details: add a token to ve allowed for staking

params._tokenAddress: 1. address of the new allowed token

allSLAs().details: public view function that returns all the service level agreements

params._messengerAddress: 1. the address of the chainlink messenger contract
params._networkNames: 5. array of bytes32 with the names of the valid networks
params._sla_week_period_ends: 4. array of the ends of the weeks period
params._sla_week_period_starts: 3. array of the starts of the weeks period

createSLA(address,string,uint256[]).details: public function for creating canonical service level agreements

params._canonicalPeriodIds: 6. array of allowed canonical period ids
params._ipfsHash: 4. string with the ipfs hash that contains extra information about the service level agreement

getActivePool(address).details: returns the active pools owned by a user.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

publishAnalyticsHash(bytes32,bytes32,uin.details: Receives the data from the Messenger contract

params._ipfsHash: 1. id of the canonical period to be analyzed

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
